Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[In recent days the reported number of cases from Turkey have increased markedly -- and additional 30 000 daily beginning 26 Nov 2020 (as per Worldometer data). Calculating the comparative 7-day averages as of 29 Nov 2020, there has been a 374% increase in reported cases... but remembering that the decision was made to count positive tests, thereby including pre-symptomatic cases as well as asymptomatic infections. The government has decided to impose stricter restrictions in response to increasing hospital occupancies combined with the increase in confirmed infections. A difficult decision, but an attempt to flatten the curve so hospitals aren't overwhelmed. These are difficult times. - Mod.MPP]

