[The number of countries and territories reporting confirmed cases of COVID-19 to WHO remains at 218 (Samoa has not been added).

Data by country, area, or territory for 30 Nov 2020 can be accessed at https://promedmail.org/wp-content/uploads/world-pdf/WHO%20daily%20tablesNov30_1606767528.pdf.

- The Americas region reported 47.4% of daily case numbers and 38.4% of the daily deaths reported in the past 24 hours but maintained its position as the most severely affected region, having reported more than 26.4 million cases. The USA continues to dominate, followed by Brazil, Mexico, Colombia, Argentina, and Canada. Other countries reporting more than 1000 cases include Peru, Panama, Chile, and Ecuador. And countries/territories reporting more than 500 cases but fewer than 1000 in the past 24 hours include Dominican Republic, and Paraguay. Costa Rica did not report any newly confirmed cases in the past 24 hours.

- The European region reported 33.3% of daily case numbers and 41.3% of the daily deaths reported in the past 24 hours, and total cumulative cases reported exceed 18.6 million. Countries not reporting cases today (30 Nov 2020) include Spain, Israel, Switzerland, Sweden, Kazakhstan, and Norway, among others. Countries reporting more than 10 000 cases in the past 24 hours include Russia, Italy, UK, Poland, and Germany. There are 19 additional countries reporting more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours.

- The Eastern Mediterranean region reported 6.9% of daily case numbers and 9.8% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 4.08 million cases. Iran is dominant, with continuing highs above 10 000, followed by Morocco, Jordan, Pakistan, Palestinian Authority, Iraq, Tunisia, Lebanon, UAE, and Libya. Sudan and Somalia have not reported any cases in the past 24 hours.

- The African region reported 1.1% of daily case numbers and 0.79% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours and has reported more than 1.50 million cases. South Africa maintains its dominance, followed by Kenya, Ethiopia, Cameroon, Uganda, Ghana, Zimbabwe, Mali and Reunion. Algeria did not report any new cases in the past 24 hours.

- The Western Pacific region reported 1.2% of daily case numbers and 0.77% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of 0.88 million cases. Japan is dominant, followed by Philippines, Malaysia, South Korea, China, Guam, and Mongolia.

- The South East Asia region reported 10.1% of the daily newly reported cases and 9.0% of reported deaths in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 10.7 million cases. As previously, India remains dominant, followed by Indonesia, Bangladesh, Nepal, and Myanmar.

Impression: Basically unchanged on the regional levels with the continued dominance of Europe and the Americas region representing over 80% of both newly confirmed cases and newly reported deaths in the past 24 hours, even with reduced reports over the weekend. At the country level, Japan is the dominant country in the Western Pacific region; Italy and Russia are dominant in the European region. The USA maintains its position as the country reporting the most cases on a daily basis.

On the Overview tab at the WHO source URL, the epidemic curve of confirmed COVID-19 cases by WHO region, 30 Dec 2019 through 29 Nov 2020, is an excellent visual representation of the pandemic. - Mod.MPP]

