[In the past 24 hours, the USA (169 466), Turkey (31 219), India (31 179), and Russia (26 338) have reported the highest numbers of cases. A global total of 8693 deaths were reported in the past 24 hours (29-30 Nov 2020). Countries not reporting newly confirmed cases in the past 24 hours include Sweden and Bolivia among others.

Countries reporting more than 10 000 newly confirmed cases in the past 24 hours (10 countries) include the USA, Turkey, India, Russia, Brazil (21 538), Spain (18 753), Italy (16 376), Germany (14 156), Iran (13 321), and UK (12 330). A total of 54 countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours (down from 64 on Fri 27 Nov 2020); 27 of the 54 countries reporting more than 1000 newly confirmed cases are from the European region, 10 are from the Americas region, 8 are from the Eastern Mediterranean region, 5 are from the South East Asia region, 3 are from the Western Pacific region, and 1 is from the African region.

Comparing the 7-day averages of daily confirmed cases from the past 7 days (581 660) and those from 8-14 days ago, case counts have decreased by 2.3%, while daily reported deaths (10 266) have increased by 3.0%. The USA has decreased both newly confirmed cases (-7.8%) and reported deaths (-3.5%) which may still be a function of the weekend decreased reporting. The 7-day average daily new cases reported in the USA is 163 242 and newly reported deaths is 1521.

Impression: The countries in the European and the Americas regions are still showing the largest increases in daily new case counts, followed by the Eastern Mediterranean and the South East Asia regions. - Mod.MPP]
